Unzip the SeriesForExport zip file
Start ENVI
In the Toolbox start Spatiaotemporal Analysis/Build Raster Series using a double click
In the tool uncheck Order by Time
Leave Display result checked (or not)
Click on Add Raster
Select Add Filename
Navigate to the unzipped series folder
There are two series in this folder: one for 2CMV and another for Cloud Mask
When displayed in ENVI the cloud mask images should be displayed on top of the 2CMV images

Select all the 2CMV files with this prefix: CMV_ENVITemp
Click on Open
In the tool create a new filename with "CMV" in the folder of your choice with the ".series" extension
Click on Save
Click on OK in the tool
The 2CMV series will be created and displayed in the ENVI UI

Restart the Spatiaotemporal Analysis/Build Raster Series using a double click
In the tool uncheck Order by Time
Leave Display result checked (or not)
Click on Add Raster
Select Add Filename
Navigate to the unzipped series folder
Select all the cloud files that have this prefix: CLD_ENVITemp
Click on Open
In the tool create a new filename in the folder of your choice with the ".series" extension
Click on Save
Click on OK in the tool
The cloud series will be created and displayed in the ENVI UI.
In the Stretch drop down menu select No Stretch (replacing the default 2% Stretch)
Set transparency to 75%

In the Series manager tool click on the three bar hamburger symbol
Select Link to the CMV_ENVITemp series
Click on the play arrow
Set speed to your preferred rate
Zoom out to view the entire dataset

Open the World_Countries shape file as follows:
Unzip the World Countries zip file
In ENVI select File/Open
Navigate to within the unzipped folder and open World_Countries_Generalized.shp
